  "riddle": "1. Unearth the tale of a notable pitcher from the early 20th century, whose days ended at a specific age. Seek the page that chronicles Biff Schlitzer's life and find this final number.\n\n2. A team from the city of good neighbors once claimed glory in its league. How many championships did this proud franchise hoist in its fleeting existence?\n\n3. Consider the journey from the sprawling region celebrated for its natural beauty to the bustling city known for its wings. What is the distance, in miles, that would separate these two places?\n\n4. In what year did the league come into existence, shattering the conventions of professional baseball? Discover this critical date!\n\n5. The annals of baseball from a certain year detail numerous moments of excitement. How many distinct monthly sections are noted in the document devoted to that eventful year?\n\n6. From the number you uncovered in clue 5, what is the total count of distinct factors that constitute this figure?\n\n7. Imagine a critical component of a baseball field where pitchers find their footing. This spot is a set distance from home plate to the outfield barricade. What is that range, expressed in feet?\n\n8. If zero kilometers were to be transformed, how many miles would that equate to? Find this curious conversion.\n\n9. Delve into the metrics of performance; on what base count does the earned run average factor innings for each game? This key anchoring number is what you seek.\n\n10. Seek out the elevation of nine—how high does this numerical landmark rise above sea level?\n\n11. By determining how many institutions of higher learning are situated near this numerical range, what total do you uncover? \n\n12. Combine the elevation you uncovered in clue 10 with the count of academic establishments from clue 11. What new value emerges from your findings?\n\n13. A name tied to a crucial statistic flaunts its melodic structure. Count the vowels you find within this appellation, and reveal the to